The issue with your code is that you are trying to write to a file using a DataOutputStream, but the file does not exist. This is causing an IOException to be thrown, which is being caught and the message "No file exist" is being printed to the console.

To fix this issue, you should first create the file using a FileOutputStream before trying to write to it with a DataOutputStream. You can do this by adding the following line of code before the for loop:
```arduino
DataOutputStream out = new DataOutputStream(new FileOutputStream("C:\\data.txt"));
```
This will create the file "data.txt" in the specified directory if it does not already exist. Then you can write to the file as you have done in your code.

Here is the updated code:
```arduino
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class DataStreams {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        DataOutputStream out = new DataOutputStream(new FileOutputStream("C:\\data.txt"));
        for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
            out.write(i);
        }
        out.close();
    }
}
```
This code should create a file "data.txt" containing the numbers 0 to 9.
